Before proceeding let us elaborate a bit on variations of critical pair conditions for
ensuring conuence of left-linear TRSs. Huet's result above states that
(1) s␀␀k!t for every critical pair hs; ti of R
suces for ensuring conuence. Surprisingly, it still seems to be unknown whether any
of the following conditions also suces (see [DJK91], Problem 13 of J.-J. Levy).
(2) s␀␀k!t or t␀␀k!s, for every critical pair hs; ti of R.
(3) s!
=
