Clearly, the following implications hold between these conditions: (5) =) (3) =) (2),
(5) =) (4) =) (2). We remark that due to Theorem 3.2 potential counterexamples
for (3) and (5) would have to be (besides left-linear) non-right-linear, non-terminating
and non-orthogonal, hence overlapping. Unfortunately, our approach developed below
does not solve any of these open problems.
