Intuitively, the observations above suggest to analyse more carefully local divergences
where in one parallel step several (parallel) redex positions are critical w.r.t. the other
step. From a more abstract point of view this means to study the following questions:
(1) What are critical peaks / pairs for the parallel reduction relation?
(2) Which conditions on the corresponding critical peaks / pairs for parallel reduction
guarantee strong conuence?
For (1) we shall introduce the notion of parallel critical peaks / pairs. In fact, Denition
4.1 below only accounts for critical divergences of the form t
1
