Since non-overlapping TRSs have no critical pairs, hence also no parallel critical pairs,
we obtain as a direct consequence of Theorem 4.11 the following well-known result.
Corollary 4.12 (cf. e.g. [Ros73])
Any orthogonal TRS is conuent.
